
[1]costive

   COSTIVE, a. [L, to cram, to stuff.]

   1. Literally, crowded, stuffed, as the intestines; hence, bound in
   body; retaining fecal matter in the bowels, in a hard and dry state;
   having the excrements obstructed, or the motion of the bowels too slow.

   2. Dry and hard; as costive clay. [Not used.]
